 content description 
dir controllers -> Controllers folder will contain all the controllers for the SMETH application SMETHAcknowledgementController, SMETHAttachmentController, SMETHComposeMessageController, SMETHOptionController, SMETHReadMessageController, SMETHReportController and SMETHRequestController will all be moved there.
dir preferences -> Preferences contains XUL documents displayed in the Smeth Preference window.
dir preferences subdur controllers -> Controllers for each of the panes displayed in the Smeth Preference window.
dir xml -> XML folder contains all the XMl template that is use while composing a SEPAmail message.
dir xsl -> XSL folder contains all the xsl that is use for transformations in Smeth.
 SMETHAcknowledgementController.js -> SMETHAcknowledgementController is reponsible for the generation of acknowledgement missive, handles the sending of automatic and manual acknowledgements.
 SMETHAttachmentController.js -> SMETHAcknowledgementController is reponsible for the displaying, handling the save and open for SEPAmail documents.
 SMETHComposeMessageController.js -> SMETHComposeMessageController is the class that is attached to SMETHComposeMessageView, it helps in the setting up the composition windows for the composition of different type of SEPAmail messages.
 SMETHComposeMessageView.xul -> SMETHComposeMessageView is the overlay of the thunderbird "messengercompose" view, it helps use to modify the compose window user interface and to attach custom javascript.
 SMETHOptionController.js
 SMETHOptionView.xul
 SMETHReadMessageController.js -> SMETHReadMessageController is the class that is attached to SMETHReadMessageView, it helps in the setting up the readng pane for the different type of SEPAmail messages.
 SMETHReadMessageView.xul
 SMETHReportController.js -> SMETHReportController is the class that is responsible for the composition and sending of SEPAmail reports(Simple Test and Activation)
 SMETHRequestController.js -> SMETHReportController is the class that is responsible for the composition and sending of SEPAmail requests(Simple Test and Activation)
 smethWidgets.xml -> XBL components used in Smeth




 